data.description: RU a new? Have you heard about Douglass, historically known as the women's college at Rutgers? RU looking for a supportive community that will help you hit the ground running and get the most of your time here? Come check out Douglass where we focus on women's leadership by providing special opportunities for you to build your skills and surround yourself with students and staff who are passionate about social justice and centering women's lived experiences.  Meet new and current Douglass students and staff and hear about the opportunities and experiences that will enhance your college journey. From social events like International Women's Day to internship and research opportunities, Douglass enhances all majors and helps you build your resume and connections. Don't miss food and Douglass swag!! data.description: Join the Center for Women in the Arts at Douglass for a workshop led by acclaimed artist Liz Collins! This unique needlepoint workshop invites you to explore the meditative joy of stitching. Collins will guide participants through the myriad of stitches possible within needlepoint and share her distinctive methodology for creating improvisational designs, treating needlepoint as a slow drawing process in response to the grid.   Only open to Douglass and Art & Design students. Free supplies and snacks provided! Supplies are limited – First come, first served. All skill levels and forms of stitching are welcome and supported. This experience counts towards the Douglass Discovery curriculum requirement. R3: Career/Discovery/Professional Development/Research. Reminder: To receive DRC curriculum credit, you must complete a reflection survey. *Liz Collins is the 2025-2026 Estelle Lebowitz & Ann Beneduce-Lebowitz Artist-in-Residence. Her solo exhibition, Shapeshifter, is on view through March 13, 2026 in the Mary H. Dana Women Artists Series Galleries at Douglass Libraries. ___ * Image and Media ReleaseBy attending this event, you acknowledge and agree that Rutgers University may photograph, record, or otherwise capture your artwork, image, and/or voice.
